              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f:A\vdash  B]]></fr:tex> be a morphism in a deductive system <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex>. We say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <html:em>(thunkably, linearly) invertible</html:em> when there exists a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004N.xml" title="Linear and thunkable inverses" addr="jms-004N" type="local">(thunkable, linear) inverse</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
