            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0048.xml" title="Deductive system" addr="jms-0048" type="local">deductive system</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> is called <html:em>positively univalent</html:em> when for any positive <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\in \mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex>, the type of positive objects <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\in \mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> equipped with a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004R.xml" title="Thunkably and linearly invertible maps" addr="jms-004R" type="local">thunkably invertible</fr:link> <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-004A.xml" title="Linear and thunkable maps" addr="jms-004A" type="local">thunkable</fr:link> map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f:B\vdash  A]]></fr:tex> is contractible.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
